"<ac:layout>
  <ac:layout-section ac:type=\"single\">
    <ac:layout-cell>
      <p>Gate DVx is a major step where actual product development take place.</p>
      <p>Gate DVx might cover several design verification stages which are numbered as DV1, DV2, DV3 and etc.</p>
      <p>Thus Gate DVx also numerical and could be called Gate DVx.1, DVx.2, DVx.3 and etc.</p>
      <p>In case when Gate DVx number in a sequence is 1, then steps will be numbered G.DVx1.x, in case when it is 2 - G.DVx2.x.</p>
      <p>Gate DVx always ends with physical prototype of electronics made (if project consist of hardware to be developed).</p>
      <p>See full descriptions of the points here: <a href=\"https://<CONFLUENCE_HOST>/display/PMO/Gate+DVx+Description\">DVx Description</a>
      </p>
    </ac:layout-cell>
  </ac:layout-section>
